# Loctran repository rules

## Repository hygiene
- Never create random Markdown files in the root directory. Maintain strict open-source repository hygiene. Do not commit internal AI thought processes to the codebase.
- Store agent guidance only in this file.
- Keep generated or local-only artifacts out of version control.

## Engineering standards
- Use type hints on public Python functions.
- Keep code ruff-clean and format with `ruff format`.
- Prefer `pathlib.Path` over string path manipulation.
- Use async patterns for I/O-bound server code.
- Avoid polling for critical realtime state when WebSockets are available.

## Safety and portability
- Validate user-provided paths and keep file operations inside allowed directories.
- Keep behavior cross-platform (macOS, Linux, Windows).
- Use clear logging and do not swallow exceptions.
